{[#]Black has carried out ...b6-b5 under favorable circumstances and White's
wish to prevent ...b5-b4 has weakened c4. With} 20. Bf1 {he intended to
inhibit the invasion. Does this really work?} Nbc4 $1 {For hidden tactical
reasons this is stronger than White had thought.} 21. Nxc4 (21. Bxc4 bxc4 $17 {
followed by ...Nd3 is also bad for White.}) 21... Bg5 $1 $17 {The point. Since
20.Bf1 has left f3 undefended the last move wins material.} (21... Nxc4 $2 22.
Bxc4 bxc4 23. Ne2 $5 $11 {would leave White with satisfactory stability on the
dark squares.}) 22. Nxe5 Bxf4 23. Nxc6 Bxc1 24. Nxb8 Bxb2 25. Nxb5 Rcxb8 26.
Rb1 Bxa3 27. Rb3 Bc1 28. Nxd6 Ra4 29. b5 Ba3 30. Nc4 Bc5 31. Ne5 Ra2 32. Rf3
Rd8 33. Bc4 Rc2 34. Bb3 Rb2 35. Kg2 Rdd2 36. Nd3 Rxb3 37. Nxc5 Rxf3 0-1

