{[#]Black is very active, but his b-pawn seems to be in danger. How to develop
the initiative?} 34... Nde5 $1 35. Qb1 (35. fxe5 dxe5 $19 {retrieves the piece
with a decisive advantage.}) 35... Nc4 $17 {Once the knight has occupied this
square White is practically doomed. The b5-pawn is taboo because of the
hanging b2-bishop and the complications initiated by White will turn against
him.} 36. Nxc6 Nxb2 37. e5 Nxd1 38. Qxd1 (38. Ne7+ Bxe7 39. Bxa8 Nxc3 $19 {
leaves the queen alone against a whole black army.}) 38... Rxc6 39. exf6 Qc8
40. Bxc6 Qxc6+ 41. Ne4 Qxe4+ $1 0-1

