{[#]After the typical} 19... d5 20. e5 {Black came up with the surprising} Nxe5
21. Qxe5 Qxe5 22. Rxe5 Ne4 {Evaluate the position.} 23. Rxe4 $2 {Equivalent to
surrendering.} ({White should have sacrificed the exchange with} 23. Nxe4 $1
dxe4 24. Bxe4 Bxe5 ({Or if} 24... f6 $5 25. Bxb7 fxe5 26. Bxa6 exd4 27. Bb5 Re7
28. Kg2 e5 29. Ba3 Rc7 {Parrying c4-c5.} 30. Bb4 {Planning a4-a5.} Bf8 31. Bd2
Ra8 32. b4 {followed by a4-a5 with adequate compensation.}) 25. Bxb7 Re7 (25...
Rd6 26. f4 Bf6 27. b4 {is similar.}) 26. Bxa6 Red7 27. a5 $1 bxa5 28. c5 {
due to the threat c5-c6-c7 Black has nothing better than} Rxd4 $11 {with a
draw.}) 23... dxe4 24. Nde2 {Black played} f5 $6 $15 {and won a long game.} ({
Instead,} 24... Rxd1+ $1 25. Nxd1 Rd8 26. Nec3 Rd2 {would have been decisive.})
0-1

