{[#]Black met} 17. f4 {with} e5 {without spending time on ...g7-g6 and thus
showing that he did not fear} 18. Nf5 {What justified his optimism?} d5 $1 {
[%cal Gf8c5] Threatening to pin the queen with ...Bc5.} 19. fxe5 Bc5 20. Nd4
Nxe4 21. Nxd5 Qxe5 22. b4 Bf8 {After dissolving White's center Black's play is
more pleasant, but White should be able to maintain the equality.} 23. Qxe4
Qxe4 24. Bxe4 Rxe4 25. Nc3 $2 ({The correct move order was} 25. Nf5 $1 {
threatening among others Bxg7.} g6 26. Nc3 $1 Re6 27. Rxd7 Bc6 28. Rd5 gxf5 29.
Rxf5 Bxb4 30. Nd5 {with simplifications and a probable draw.}) 25... Ree8 $17 {
Now White's position is in ruins.} 26. Nf5 Ne5 27. Nd5 Bxd5 28. cxd5 Rxc1 29.
Bxc1 Bxb4 30. Kg2 f6 31. Nd4 Rd8 32. Nf3 Nc4 33. Rd4 b5 34. a4 Bc5 35. Rd3 b4
0-1

