{[#]The game went} 17... e5 18. Nd5 {Your move.} Qd8 $1 ({It makes no sense to
allow the knight's access to c6 with} 18... Nxd5 19. exd5 Bf6 20. g5 Bg7 21.
Nc6 {with uncertain play. The game continuation offers Black an advantage.})
19. Ne2 ({The point is that the generally desirable exchange} 19. Nxe7+ Qxe7 {
activates the queen whilst leaving several white pawns hanging.} 20. fxe5 (20.
Ne2 Nxe4 $17) (20. Nb3 exf4 $19) 20... dxe5 21. Nb3 Rfd8 {Black defends the
knight threatening to take on b4 without fearing g4-g5. There is also a newly
created threat, ...Nc5 so White cannot save his b4-pawn. If} 22. g5 Ne8 $17 {
the g5-pawn is hanging too.}) 19... Bxd5 $6 ({Overestimating the next move. It
would have been better to keep c6 defended with} 19... Nxd5 $1 20. exd5 {
in order to be able to play} exf4 21. Nxf4 Ne5 {Attacking c4} 22. Re4 Bh4 $17 {
with great play on the dark squares.}) 20. exd5 (20. cxd5 Rxc1 21. Qxc1 exf4
22. Qxf4 Ne5 $15) 20... e4 (20... exf4 21. Nd4 $16) 21. Bg2 $2 (21. Nd4 $1 exf3
22. Nc6 Rxc6 23. dxc6 Nxg4 {leads to unclear consequences.}) 21... Nxg4 22.
Bxe4 Nxf2 23. Kxf2 b5 {Everything is basically over now.} 24. cxb5 Bh4+ 25. Ng3
Qb6+ 26. Kg2 Qxb5 27. Qb3 Bxg3 28. hxg3 Rxc1 29. Rxc1 Qe2+ 30. Kh3 Qxe4 31. a4
Nf6 32. Rd1 Re8 33. b5 Qf5+ 34. Kg2 Re2+ 35. Kf1 Qe4 0-1

