1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. Nc3 e6 4. g3 b6 5. Bg2 Bb7 6. O-O a6 7. d4 cxd4 8. Qxd4
d6 9. Rd1 Be7 10. Ng5 Bxg2 11. Kxg2 Nc6 12. Qf4 O-O 13. b3 {Abstractly the
most consistent move. White continues developing and keeps both knight jumps
to e4 in reserve.} Ra7 14. Bb2 h6 ({Or else Black can continue regrouping:} 
14... Qa8 15. Kg1 h6 16. Nge4 Ne8 (16... Re8 $2 {Ribli,Z (2585)-Ftacnik,L 
(2475) Dubai 1986 (½-½, 22) allows} 17. Nxd6) 17. Rac1 b5 $11) 15. Nf3 ({
We already know that} 15. Nge4 {is not one-sided:} Rd7 16. Rab1 $5 {/\a4, ><b3:
Krasenkow,M (2560)-Brodsky,M (2520) Rostov on Don 1993 (½-½, 59)} Nh7 $5 ({
With the d6-pawn defended Black can deviate from the normal} 16... Ne8 {
which is also good.}) 17. Nd2 ({A possible continuation showing one of the
ideas behind ...Nh7 is} 17. a4 $2 f5 18. Nd2 Bg5 19. Qf3 Ne5 20. Qh5 g6 21. Qh3
Bxd2 22. Rxd2 Ng5 23. Qh4 Qa8+ 24. Kg1 Nef3+) 17... Bg5 18. Qf3 (18. Qe4 d5 19.
cxd5 exd5 {creates a strong central pawn with obvious white initiative.}) 18...
Ne5 19. Qe4 f5 20. Qc2 Qa8+ 21. Nf3 Bf6 $132 {[%cal Gh7g5] /\...Ng5}) 15... Rd7
{Consolidating the d6-pawn before looking for a good square for the queeen.} (
15... Qb8 16. Ne4 Nxe4 ({I prefer} 16... Ne8 17. Rac1 f5 18. Nc3 Bf6 $132) 17.
Qxe4 Rc8 18. Rac1 {1/2-1/2 Adorjan,A (2535)-Ftacnik,L (2500)/Esbjerg 1985/EXT
2000}) ({If Black is in a hurry to regroup with the queen I would prefer} 15...
Qa8 {setting up pressure along the long diagonal.} 16. Ne4 Ne8 17. Rac1 f5 18.
Nc3 g5 19. Qe3 Ne5 20. Kg1 f4 21. gxf4 gxf4 22. Qe4 Qxe4 23. Nxe4 Nxf3+ 24.
exf3 Rf5 $11) 16. Rac1 Qb8 ({Once again} 16... Qa8 {is an important
alternative and if} 17. Ne4 Ne8 $11 {Compare with the main line below.} 18. c5
bxc5 19. Nxc5 Rc7 $11) 17. Ne4 Nxe4 ({Due to his concrete major piece
placement Black should now avoid} 17... Ne8 $6 {due to} 18. c5 bxc5 (18... d5
19. Ne5 Nxe5 20. Bxe5 Qa7 21. c6 $16) 19. Nxc5 Ra7 {Unfortunately the a6-pawn
is hanging.} 20. Nd7 $5 {And now the c6-knight appears to be vulnerable.} Rxd7
21. Rxc6 Qb5 22. Qc4 $14) 18. Qxe4 Rc8 19. Rd2 {½-½ Adorjan,A (2515)
-Gheorghiu,F (2520), Thessaloniki 1984} Qb7 20. h4 Rdc7 $11 {[%cal Gc6d8,Gb6b5]
followed by ...b6-b5 soon, possibly after a knight retreat to d8 or a7.} *

