1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. Nc3 e6 4. g3 b6 5. Bg2 Bb7 6. O-O a6 7. d4 cxd4 8. Qxd4
d6 9. Rd1 Be7 10. Bg5 {An active developing move leading to a series of
important tabiyas.} Nbd7 11. Bxf6 $5 {Since Black can re-capture with his
knight, keeping d6 well defended, this looks like a positional concession, but
White has dynamic ideas in mind.} Nxf6 12. Na4 Rb8 $1 {Defending the pawn
indirectly.} ({If} 12... O-O 13. Qxb6 Qxb6 14. Nxb6 Rab8 {more or less
retrieves the pawn but under unfavorable circumstances:} 15. c5 $1 (15. Na4 Bc6
16. b3 Bxa4 17. bxa4 Rfc8 $11) 15... dxc5 16. Nc4 $14 {Hergott,D (2385)
-Ionescu,C (2440) Novi Sad 1990 (½-½, 41)}) 13. c5 dxc5 (13... Bxf3 14. Bxf3
dxc5 {avoids the complications but leaves Black slightly worse:} 15. Qe5 Qc8
16. Rd6 (16. Bc6+ Kf8 17. Bf3 h5 $5 $13) 16... O-O (16... Bxd6 17. Qxd6 Nd5 18.
Bxd5 exd5 19. Nxb6 Rxb6 20. Qxb6 O-O 21. Rc1 c4 22. b3 $14) 17. Rxb6 Rxb6 18.
Nxb6 Qd8 19. Nc4 $14 {Kortschnoj,V (2695)-Gheorghiu,F (2540) Sao Paulo 1979 
(½-½, 31) True, it is not easy to prove anything concrete here.}) (13... bxc5
14. Nxc5 $14 dxc5 $2 15. Qa4+ Nd7 16. Ne5 Bd5 (16... Bc8 17. Nxd7 Bxd7 18. Rxd7
Qxd7 19. Bc6 $18) 17. Bxd5 $16) 14. Qe5 Bd5 15. e4 {The only way to maintain
the rhythm of the initiative.} Nxe4 ({Black needs to pick up the gauntlet as
after} 15... Bd6 $6 {White has} 16. Rxd5 $1 Nxd5 17. Qxg7 Qf6 18. Qxf6 Nxf6 19.
e5 Be7 20. exf6 Bxf6 21. Rc1 $14 {with a small material advantage, Hergott,D 
(2395)-Pineault,D (2240) Quebec 1997 (1-0, 37)}) 16. Qxg7 Bf6 17. Qh6 {The
only way to keep the queen active.} (17. Qg4 $2 b5 18. Ne5 h5 19. Qe2 bxa4 20.
Bxe4 Bxe5 21. Bxd5 Bd4 22. Bc6+ Kf8 $17 {followed by ...Qg5 and ...h5-h4.}) {
Objectively Black is OK, but he needs to choose the safest continuation from a
practical point of view. Or else, if he is heading for uncompromising play,
try to grab more material and hope to survive the attack.} 17... Qe7 (17... b5
18. Ne5 (18. Ne1 Nxf2 $5 19. Kxf2 bxa4 20. Bxd5 {Hoensch,M (2315)-Jurek,J 
(2390) Wuerttemberg 1998 (1-0, 31)} exd5 21. Nd3 Bd4+ 22. Kg2 Qf6 $17) (18. Nc3
Nxc3 19. bxc3 Bxc3 20. Rac1 Qf6 $17 {David,P (2440)-Lechtynsky,J (2430) Brno
1990 (½-½, 41)}) 18... Bxe5 19. Bxe4 Qf6 20. Qxf6 Bxf6 21. Nxc5 Rc8 ({
White's compensation after} 21... Bxe4 22. Nxe4 Bxb2 23. Rab1 Ba3 {should
suffice only for a draw.} 24. Rb3 Be7 25. Rc3 Rd8 26. Rxd8+ Kxd8 27. Rc6 Kd7
28. Rxa6 Rc8 $11) 22. Bxd5 Rxc5 23. Bb7 O-O 24. Rac1 Rxc1 25. Rxc1 Bxb2 26. Rc2
$11 {½-½ Sadilek,P (2202)-Jurek,J (2354) Aschach 2010}) 18. Rac1 c4 (18... b5
{once again allows some turbulences:} 19. Nxc5 Nxc5 20. Rxc5 Bxf3 21. Bxf3 Qxc5
22. Qxf6 Rg8 23. Kg2 $44 {Black is an exchange up but with his rooks
uncoordinated and the king in the center he needs to be careful.}) 19. Qe3 Qb7
(19... b5 {is likely to leave White with some light initiative:} 20. Nd4 $1 (
20. Nb6 Qc5 21. Nxd5 exd5 $15) 20... bxa4 21. Bxe4 O-O 22. Bxd5 exd5 23. Qxe7
Bxe7 24. Nc6 Bg5 25. f4 Rb6 26. Ne5 {and Black is still hanging a bit.}) (19...
O-O $6 20. Nxb6 Bxb2 21. Rc2 $1 Bg7 22. Nd2 $1 $14 {Hergott,D-Suba,M
L'Hospitalet de l'Infante op 1993 (1-0, 30)}) 20. Nd2 (20. Ne1 Bg5 $5 21. f4
Bf6 $15 {To retrieve the pawn White needs to give up his remaining bishop but
this will leave the king very exposed.}) (20. Rxd5 exd5 21. Nd2 Bg5 22. f4 Be7
23. Nxe4 dxe4 24. Bxe4 Qc7 25. Kg2 b5 $17 {does not offer White compensation
for the exchange, as Black's queenside is very threatening.}) 20... Nxd2 21.
Bxd5 Qxd5 22. Rxd2 Qg5 $5 ({The point behind "losing a tempo" is revealed after
} 22... Qa5 23. Rxc4 b5 24. Qf4 $16 {In the main line the f4-square will not
be available.}) 23. f4 Qa5 24. Rxc4 (24. Nc3 O-O 25. Ne4 Bg7 26. Rxc4 Qxa2 {
With his king exposed, too, White may have problems to prove full compensation
for the pawn.}) 24... O-O $5 {The most ambitious.} ({After} 24... b5 {White
has nothing better than reaching a draw with a few only moves:} 25. Rc5 Qxa4
26. Rf5 Be7 27. Qe5 O-O 28. Rg5+ Bxg5 29. Qxg5+ {with a draw by perpetual.})
25. Nc3 Rbd8 {Black has pressure against the queenside and will soon control
the d-file. Despite his kingside structural problems, he should be not worse 
(the white king is also exposed after all!)} *

