d6 9. Rd1 Be7 10. Be3 {This can eventually transpose to Lines 8 or 9, but less
typically can also have independent value.} Nbd7 11. Ng5 ({The aforementioned
transposition takes place after} 11. Qd2 O-O 12. Bf4) 11... Bxg2 12. Kxg2 O-O
13. Nge4 (13. Rac1 {allows Black to defend the d6-pawn without the need to
