{Both sides have carried out thorough regrouping, but Black's coordination is
more effective. The f1-rook is not playing yet and the dark-squared bishop
went back on an unnatural square in order to avoid tactical tricks based on ...
Nxe4. Black cannot improve his piece position any more which makes the next
move not only logical, but also a necessity.} 1... d5 $1 2. e5 Nfd7 3. cxd5
Nxe5 4. f4 {White must have put big hopes in this move. It seems that Black
simply loses material. But his perfect coordination also implies a high
dynamic potential, allowing the following small combination:} exd5 $1 {A nasty
trick based on Black's superior coordination.} 5. fxe5 d4 $1 6. Nxd4 Rxe5 7.
Qf2 Nd3 $1 {with strong initiative. Uhlmann,W (2555)-Gheorghiu,F (2540) Manila
1976 (0-1, 43)} *

